#: src-ru/data/events_cards.xml.rawclobber:101
msgid ""
"data/events_cards.xml.rawclobber$//textList[@name=\"RULES_BLACK_JACK\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"The goal of the game is to beat the dealer by having more points than them. "
"Number cards are worth their face value, J-Q-K are 10 points, and A is 1 or "
"11. You cannot exceed 21 points—that is a bust. Both the player and dealer "
"are dealt 2 cards face up. If the player gets 21 points in the first two "
"cards (\"blackjack\") and the dealer has less, the player gets a 1.5x "
"payout. If the dealer has blackjack and the player doesn't, the player "
"loses. If no one has blackjack, the player can hit until they bust (loss, "
"bet goes to dealer) or decide to stop. Then the dealer draws cards to at "
"least 17 points (even if they already have more than the player) until they "
"bust or reach 17. Points are compared, and the bet goes to the one with the "
"highest total. In all tie cases, the bet is returned."

