#: src-ru/data/events_cards.xml.rawclobber:4182
msgid "data/events_cards.xml.rawclobber$//textList[@name=\"RULES_POKER\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"The goal of the game is to beat the dealer by having a better hand combination. There are 10 combinations in increasing order of strength:\n"
"1. High Card (strongest card in hand - A)\n"
"2. Pair (2 cards of same rank - 88)\n"
"3. Two Pair (2 cards of same rank, 2 of another - QQ55)\n"
"4. Three of a Kind (3 cards of same rank - KKK)\n"
"5. Straight (5 consecutive cards - 10JQKA)\n"
"6. Flush (5 cards of the same suit)\n"
"7. Full House (3 cards of same rank, 2 of another - JJ777)\n"
"8. Four of a Kind (4 cards of same rank - JJJJ)\n"
"9. Straight Flush (5 consecutive cards of the same suit - 56789)\n"
"10. Royal Flush (5 consecutive cards 10JQKA of the same suit)\n"
"An Ace can act as a 1 for straights (A2345, but not QKA23). At the start, 2 cards are dealt to the dealer, 2 to the player, and 5 shared (3 face up). The player can call, raise, or fold. The dealer responds, raises, or folds, and the next card is revealed. If the player didn't raise, the dealer can, requiring the player to call to continue. The cycle repeats until all cards are revealed. If combinations are tied, the high cards in them are compared. If they are equal, kickers are compared. Winner takes the pot. In case of a tie, the pot is split."

